rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0001
rows.name:
It's been nearly 50 years since Gula
was placed under Superbian rule.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0002
rows.name:
Gula used to have its own army, you know.
My old man was a high-ranking officer in it.
Doesn't look like much now, though.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0003
rows.name:
The Gulan army was disbanded after our defeat.
Now there are only small self-defense corps
for each tribe.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0004
rows.name:
At a glance, it might seem like we're being ruled,
but you could also say we're being protected
from other nations.

rows.label: tlk41700121_02_msg0005
rows.name:
Superbia doesn't interfere with Gulan culture.
As long as they protect that, you could say it's an
easy enough world for Gula to live in.
